    <briefdescription>
<para>This class looks for a rotation gesture involving two touches. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>It measures the relative rotation of two touch points &amp; emits a signal when this changes. Please see <ref refid="classDali_1_1RotationGesture" kindref="compound">RotationGesture</ref> for more information.</para>
<para>The application programmer can use this gesture detector as follows: <programlisting><codeline><highlight class="normal"><ref refid="classDali_1_1RotationGestureDetector_1a29a8e724abcd684636a91ea7d221daf6" kindref="member">RotationGestureDetector</ref><sp/>detector<sp/>=<sp/><ref refid="classDali_1_1RotationGestureDetector_1a3473c560b98f40038da7532dfa7570ca" kindref="member">RotationGestureDetector::New</ref>();</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">detector.Attach(<sp/>myActor<sp/>);</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">detector.DetectedSignal().Connect(<sp/></highlight><highlight class="keyword">this</highlight><highlight class="normal">,<sp/>&amp;MyApplication::OnRotation<sp/>);</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ref refid="classDali_1_1RotationGesture" kindref="compound">RotationGesture</ref></para>
</simplesect>
